title: About
text: This site is to enable you to try to navigate around some tools we use daily. This website is build using a wonderful open-source tool called quarto. The only important for this tool is that any file with .qmd will be processed and finally rendered out as the content of the webpage1. Also, the syntax is just straight up markdown syntax. Hopefully you guys are all familiar enough with markdown syntax, and navigate well on this page.

title: On Boarding for TechLauncher Students
text:
This onboarding site is here to guide you through the workflow that youâ€™ll be following starting Monday, from Week 4, Semester 1, all the way to the end of the year. Itâ€™s a long journey ahead, but weâ€™re excited to have you on board!



Pookie Logo


Letâ€™s dive in and get started.

title: On Boarding for TechLauncher Students
text:
3.1 Project Background
The concept was first conceived in September 2024 as a platform that would enhance the fields of education and hiring. After going through three Startup Pre-accelerator programs, Pookie has now changed the direction of two of its ideas. Pookie wants to completely transform the way early-stage jobseekers and students interact with small and medium-sized businesses. We tackle this by beginning as an All-in-One Career Analytics platform that links small and medium-sized businesses with job searchers.
Pookie is your best friend, created by students for students and by a small-to medium-sized business for small-to medium-sized businesses. Pookie is there for you during good times and bad. It provides you with the best job recommendations and chances because it knows you better than you do. Even opportunities you never knew you needed.

title: On Boarding for TechLauncher Students
text:
5.1 Contribution Guide
The overall contribution guide is very simple:

Open an issue for the things you are going to work on. Picking a suitable issue templates.
Open a feature branch for your issue, preferable starting with the issue number (i.e.Â in the format of [issue-number]-<description>)
Coding, coding, codingâ€¦
Make an PR from your feature branch against the main branch
Request peer-review for your code.

Note that normally you would need Sean or Isaac to review your PR, but for this demo practice, you can have one of the group members to do it.

Merge into main

It is very important to keep the main branch always work.

text:
